For the crispy pork, heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium-high heat. Season the pork strips on both sides with salt and freshly ground black pepper and fry for 8-10 minutes.Add the sesame seeds and red onion and fry for a further five minutes. Add the honey, stir well and cook for one minute, or until the pork is completely cooked through.Meanwhile, for the dressing, place all the dressing ingredients into a bowl and mix well.For the salad, place the cheese, onion, orange and herbs into a bowl and mix well. Pour over the dressing and stir to coat.To serve, place the salad onto a plate and top with the crispy pork. Serve with lime wedges and toasted ciabatta.